    Course IDCourse Description Location Timestamp
    16671 This course examines the full range of the American experience with the goal of better understanding the foundational ideals and institutions that explain the successes and limitations of the United States. This course also has interdisciplinary elements and draws deeply from political science, cultural studies, and economics to illuminate the American past, present, and future. course-description\main.js 2018-06-21T11:00:15-06:00
